g preparing invoices and collections efforts Support revenue accounting with contract review and related monthly activities to ensure compliance with ASC 606 and GAAP Record daily journal entries and perform reconciliations of various platform cash accounts Assist with the preparation and execution of the month end close Provide support for internal and external audits Maintain compliance with internal controls, policies and procedures Maintain up-to-date process documentation and procedures for all tasks Support ad hoc financial information requests and analyses and other special projects as assigned What we look for in you (ie. job requirements): Minimum of 3 years working in public accounting or in the fintech/financial services industries BA/BS in Accounting/ CPA required Expert knowledge/understanding of payment systems Possess excellent analytical skills (MS Excel), business partnering, problem solving and prioritization skills Able to work well in a dynamic environment and be able to recommend and implement process improvements, work autonomously and handle multiple tasks simultaneously Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal Strong work ethic and team player Nice to haves: Netsuite experience SQL Working with G suite Coinbase is committed to diversity in its workforce and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and to review all of our job postings to minimize biased language. Coinbase does not make hiring or employment decisions on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, sex, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, citizenship, or any other basis protected by applicable local, state or federal law. Coinbase will also consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records in a manner consistent with San Francisco\u2019s Fair Chance Ordinance and similar local laws. Global Data Privacy Notice for Job Candidates and A